description.narrative:
1. Contribute to building the EoS’ knowledge about the context in Mozambique, in terms of vulnerabilities and strengths, critical barriers and potential solutions to building resilience against and adapting to climate change and natural disasters – with a particular focus on the most vulnerable and poor groups;
2. Generate (3-4 funded Problem Statements) and publicly disseminate knowledge about vulnerabilities and strengths, critical barriers and potential solutions to building resilience against climate change and natural disasters;
3. Surface ideas to be further explored – by any/all actors and donors with an interest in climate change and;
4.Facilitate collaboration, learning and information sharing between actors in Mozambique in the field of climate change resilience and adaptation.
